      {
        "id": 105,
        "name": "David Mellis",
        "username": "david",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v2/letter/d/aeb1de/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2015-06-08T18:49:30.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>My concern about self-certification is that it\u2019s no different from simply describing a project as open-source hardware. Why add an extra layer of formality in the form of a certification, if it doesn\u2019t come with any additional assurances that a project actually open-sources what it claims to?</p>",
