      {
        "id": 125,
        "name": "phenoptix",
        "username": "phenoptix",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v2/letter/p/f07891/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2015-06-11T19:18:43.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The current process is self-certification. Those that believe they can benefit from being called open source stick the name and logo on and everyone repeats it without checking.<br>\nThere\u2019s already a definition and a logo and a community and it doesn\u2019t police itself and fact check, so why would we expect another self cert methodology to work?</p>",
        "post_number": 13,
        "post_type": 1,
